  "title": "Fairmount, Great Lakes Science Center offer new programming at Chardon location | Local Government | chagrinvalleytoday.com",
  "text": "The Fairmount Center for the Arts and Great Lakes Science Center will offer new Science, Technology, Engineering, Art and Math (STEAM) programming designed for homeschool families this fall at Fairmount’s Chardon Square location.\n“This STEAM initiative invites young learners to explore the world through experimentation, innovation and creative expression – fostering curiosity, critical thinking and collaboration in a dynamic, supportive environment,” according to a press release. “Each project-based class will be taught by Science Center educators and Fairmount teaching artists.”",
